							</p>
							<h2>Lift 2.5 Changes</h2>
							<p>
								Lift 2.5 is the first Lift with 2.10 support - has been for
								all of this year, but now it's final. 2.5 is keeping 2.9 as well.
								Named actors and a lot of other improvements to the
								<a href="http://blog.fmpwizard.com/blog/comet-actors-presentation">Comet support</a>.
								Improved jsonCall methods based on the powerful lift-json library.
							</p>
							<dl>
								<dt>Opening up of the code base:</dt>
								<dd>
									<a href="lift_modules">Modules</a>
									opened up. The Lift modules were moved to a new repository and
									organization, allowing external contributions
								</dd>
								<dd>
									<a href="https://github.com/lift/framework#pull-requests">Core lift</a>
									for small changes.
								</dd>
							</dl>


							<ul>
								<li>
									Comet improvements (named actors), library upgrades, way jQuery
									bundled, features
									around browser-to-Lift JSON processing.
								</li>
								<li>
									Improved css selector transformations using typeclasses
								</li>
								<li>
									Upgraded Squeryl to version 0.9.5
								</li>
								<li>
									Unified resource lookup (i18n), giving you the option to override
									Lift's core messages
								</li>
								<li>
									Lots of improvements to the Comet support
								</li>
								<li>
									LiftScreen now supports very flexible CSS styling
								</li>
								<li>
									Lift now uses specs2
								</li>
								<li>
									Updated Lift templates
								</li>
								<li>
									Update Scalaz library to Scalaz 7
								</li>
								<li>
									jar files built against Scala 2.9.2
								</li>
								<li>
									<a href="https://github.com/lift/framework/issues/1192">appendGLobalJs</a>
								</li>
								<li>
									<a href="https://github.com/lift/framework/pull/1352">FlexMenuBuilder</a>
									- allows you to build very flexible sitemaps
								</li>
							</ul>

